LuxExperience B.V. issued updated earnings guidance for the full fiscal year 2026, focusing expectations on the impact of its transformation plan.
The company reaffirmed that guidance will remain based on Gross Merchandise Value, with FY26 GMV now guided to a range of €2.5b to €2.7b compared with the prior range of €2.4b to €2.7b.
Management reported that the transformation plan is being executed in line with internal targets, which supports the decision to narrow the FY26 guidance ranges.
Fair value adjusted from US$10.58 to US$10.44 based on refreshed modeling work.
Revenue growth assumption revised from 14.68% to 14.17% in € terms.
Net profit margin assumption moved from 4.64% to 4.74% on € revenue.
Future P/E multiple updated from 13.83x to 13.36x on forward earnings.
Discount rate shifted from 8.29% to 8.33% as the required return on equity.
